<subSubSection id="C32AE2F2FFD1235DFF19FF72FED0FE1E" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8FB179FFD1235DFF19FF72FED0FE1E" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFF19FF72FED3FF67" bold="true" box="[199,314,186,212]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. MALE. Mesopleuron beneath without precoxal tubercle. S2 laterally with trace of felt line (a few punctures in 
<taxonomicName id="4C30CAFAFFD1235DFEF0FF17FE49FF4A" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1972" box="[302,416,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Smicromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fukudai">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFEF0FF17FE49FF4A" box="[302,416,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">P. fukudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="4C30CAFAFFD1235DFDF0FF17FD50FF4A" box="[558,697,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hylonome">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFDF0FF17FD50FF4A" box="[558,697,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">P. hylonome</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). T7 with median glabrous area. Volsella without paracuspis, at most with setose tubercle between cuspis and digitus. FEMALE. Propodeum narrower than or as broad as pronotum; scutellar scale distinct; T2 disc with two laterally disposed white to golden setal spots; T2 apex without pale setal band, rarely with sparse fringe or medially interrupted band; pygidium defined by lateral carinae and usually entirely smooth. The pygidium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C30CAFAFFD1235DFDF6FEA7FD5FFE3A" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1992" box="[552,694,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFDF6FEA7FD5FFE3A" box="[552,694,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Petersenidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually wider and defined by stronger lateral carinae than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C30CAFAFFD1235DFF49FE5BFEDBFE1E" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" box="[151,306,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Krombeinidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFF49FE5BFEDBFE1E" box="[151,306,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Krombeinidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32AE2F2FFD1235DFF19FE7FFB89FD8E" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8FB179FFD1235DFF19FE7FFB89FD8E" blockId="1.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFF19FE7FFEDDFE62" bold="true" box="[199,308,439,465]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Remarks</emphasis>
. Like 
<taxonomicName id="4C30CAFAFFD1235DFEA2FE7FFDFEFE62" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1996" box="[380,535,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Krombeinidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFEA2FE7FFDFEFE62" box="[380,535,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Krombeinidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this large genus is more reliably defined by male morphology than female. Cur- rently the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C30CAFAFFD1235DFE8BFE13FE0AFE46" authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1992" box="[341,483,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFE8BFE13FE0AFE46" box="[341,483,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Petersenidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 44 species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA1CC88FFD1235DFD0BFE13FCBDFE46" author="Lelej, A. S." box="[725,852,474,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" refId="ref2365" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2005) Catalogue of the Mutillidae (Hymenoptera) of the Oriental Region. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, 252 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lelej 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA1CC88FFD1235DFCBFFE13FBA1FE46" author="Pagliano, G. &amp; Brothers, D. J. &amp; Cambra, R. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Matteini Palmerini, M. &amp; Scaramozzino, P. L. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M." box="[865,1096,475,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" pagination="5 - 425" refId="ref2543" refString="Pagliano, G., Brothers, D. J., Cambra, R., Lelej, A. S., Lo Cascio, P., Matteini Palmerini, M., Scaramozzino, P. L., Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M. (2020) Checklist of names in Mutillidae (Hymenoptera), with illustrations of selected species. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 36 (1 - 2), 5 - 425." type="journal article" year="2020">
Pagliano 
<emphasis id="B9446D6BFFD1235DFC15FE13FBECFE46" box="[971,1029,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), which are widespread in the Oriental region and penetrate to the Eastern Palaearctic. Only 
<typeStatus id="548B0FDBFFD1235DFCBCFE37FC7BFDAA" box="[866,914,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">type</typeStatus>
species is known in both sexes, while 22 are known in male and 
<quantity id="4CC81C9CFFD1235DFEAAFDEBFE44FD8E" box="[372,429,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" unit="in" value="21.0">21 in</quantity>
females. There are no reviews or revision of this large genus.
</paragraph>
